      "text": [
        " بَيْتٍ وَاحِدٍ فَقَالَ «إِذَا كَانَ بَيْنَهُمَا قَدْرُ شِبْرٍ صَلَّتْ بِحِذَاهُ وَحْدَهَا وَ هُوَ وَحْدَهُ لاَ بَأْسَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.746 - Muawiya ibn Wahb asked Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) about a man and a woman praying in the same room.\nImam (as) said: \"If there is a space of about a handspan (shibr) between them, She may pray beside him alone and he alone; there is no harm.\""
        ]
      }
    },
